Description: Retrospective development approval for the placement of a freestanding pylon sign including LED screen installed within the Princes Highway median adjacent to the subject land. Details as follows: - 3.3m high freestanding pylon sign. - 2.5m high x 2m wide LED screen to be installed on northern elevation. The LED screen will be used to inform motorists of the products and services available from the adjacent OTR Retail Fuel Outlet. The LED screen will not be used for third party advertising. The content displayed on the LED screen will comply with DIT requirements for signage adjacent DIT controlled roads and will display static advertisements that will not flash, scroll, move or contain animation. The proposed signage is considered to be of an appropriate scale and size and is compatible with the development of the adjacent OTR site. The signage is proportional to the range of products and services available from OTR Tailem Bend. Further details are provided on the attached plans.

The LED screen will be used to inform motorists of the products and services available from the adjacent OTR Retail Fuel Outlet. The LED screen will not be used for third party advertising. The content displayed on the LED screen will comply with DIT requirements for signage adjacent DIT controlled roads and will display static advertisements that will not flash, scroll, move or contain animation. The proposed signage is considered to be of an appropriate scale and size and is compatible with the development of the adjacent OTR site. The signage is proportional to the range of products and services available from OTR Tailem Bend. Further details are provided on the attached plans.

Buildings will be moved in halves each load, 4 loads in total. 2 halves for shed 1 and half of a building for shed 2 and 3. Offices will be placed on eastern side of each shed 400mm above ground level, same as at the school. they will be setup on the same stilts as they are mounted on at the school. We will have Some planter box in front of each office. Each office will be set back 10m in from the front of each shed. For car parking 3 car can park in front of each office Building, behind the offices 3 car park along the side of the shed will angle park leaving all shed doors clear for use at anytime. Sheds are 18m from the road side so the offices will be 28m from the road, that leaves 18m from the road to each shed where vehicles coming and going can park short term safely. On the north end of each shed there is ample room to turn vehicles around etc. Business hours will be between 8.30am and 5.30pm

Property Address: Location (GDA2020) Latitude: -34°49'24.79"S, Longitude: 138°43'37.58"E This is for the Council road verge of Memorial drive from Northern end to the Southern End, as this application involves the removal trees which are a contributory item to a local heritage place
Description: Council is proposing an upgrade of Memorial Drive, which is listed as a capital works project in the 2021-22 Annual Business Plan. The works entail the reconstruction of the road, kerbs, footpaths and upgrade to the underground stormwater system. Included in these works is the opportunity to remove 20 pine trees and 1 regulated tree (tree number 11 page 19 of the Project Green report attached) and plant 68 Pin Oak trees to enhance this location as a local heritage site. Council’s Heritage Advisor, members of the RSL and members of Avenues of Honour have been instrumental in guiding and developing the upgrade proposal.
